{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EnzeujZyExapimLc8FsbKd","type":"tool_result","content":"1:\"\"\"Workflow execution engine — walks a workflow's tasks against a context.\n2:\n3:The runner is the glue between every other module in the harness:\n4:\n5:- It holds an :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.ExecutionContext` and\n6:  threads it through the task list.\n7:- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.BuiltIn`, it looks up the\n8:  named function in :data:`~darkfactory.builtins.BUILTINS` and calls\n9:  it with the context + formatted kwargs.\n10:- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.AgentTask`, it composes the\n11:  prompt via :func:`~darkfactory.templates.compose_prompt`, picks the\n12:  model (explicit override > capability mapping > sonnet fallback),\n13:  invokes Claude Code via :func:`~darkfactory.invoke.invoke_claude`,\n14:  and stores the output on the context.\n15:- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.ShellTask`, it runs the\n16:  formatted command and handles the configured ``on_failure`` policy.\n17:\n18:The runner does **not** know how to create branches, manage\n19:worktrees, or open PRs — those are built-in tasks. Its only job is\n20:the dispatch loop and the retry-on-failure bookkeeping.\n21:\n22:Retry semantics: when a ShellTask fails with\n23:``on_failure=\"retry_agent\"``, the runner looks backward in the task\n24:list for the most recent AgentTask, re-invokes it with the failed\n25:output bound to ``{{CHECK_OUTPUT}}``, and re-runs the failed shell\n26:task once. If it still fails, the runner gives up and marks the\n27:PRD blocked (via a separate ``set_status`` built-in call).\n28:\n29:Dry-run mode: when ``ctx.dry_run=True``, every built-in and shell\n30:task logs what it would do without executing. Agent tasks return a\n31:synthetic success result via :func:`~darkfactory.invoke.invoke_claude`'s\n32:``dry_run=True`` path. This is what ``prd plan`` uses.\n33:\"\"\"\n34:\n35:from __future__ import annotations\n36:\n37:import logging\n38:import subprocess\n39:from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n40:from pathlib import Path\n41:from typing import TYPE_CHECKING\n42:\n43:from .builtins import BUILTINS\n44:from .invoke import InvokeResult, capability_to_model, invoke_claude\n45:from .templates import compose_prompt\n46:from .timeouts import resolve_timeout\n47:from .workflow import (\n48:    AgentTask,\n49:    BuiltIn,\n50:    ExecutionContext,\n51:    ShellTask,\n52:    Task,\n53:    Workflow,\n54:)\n55:\n56:if TYPE_CHECKING:\n57:    from .prd import PRD\n58:    from .style import Styler\n59:\n60:\n61:logger = logging.getLogger(\"darkfactory.runner\")\n62:\n63:\n64:@dataclass\n65:class TaskStep:\n66:    \"\"\"A single executed task step and its outcome.\n67:\n68:    Used by :class:`RunResult` to record what actually happened during\n69:    a workflow run, for both success reporting and debugging failures.\n70:    \"\"\"\n71:\n72:    name: str\n73:    kind: str  # \"builtin\" | \"agent\" | \"shell\"\n74:    success: bool\n75:    detail: str = \"\"\n76:\n77:\n78:@dataclass\n79:class RunResult:\n80:    \"\"\"Structured outcome of a workflow run.\n81:\n82:    The runner populates this as it walks the task list. On success,\n83:    ``success=True`` and ``pr_url`` is set (assuming the workflow\n84:    includes a ``create_pr`` built-in). On failure, ``success=False``\n85:    and ``failure_reason`` describes what went wrong; ``steps`` is\n86:    still populated with every step that completed before the failure.\n87:    \"\"\"\n88:\n89:    success: bool\n90:    pr_url: str | None = None\n91:    steps: list[TaskStep] = field(default_factory=list)\n92:    failure_reason: str | None = None\n93:\n94:\n95:def _compute_branch_name(prd: \"PRD\") -> str:\n96:    \"\"\"Derive the branch name a workflow should use for this PRD.\n97:\n98:    Matches the convention in ``ensure_worktree``:\n99:    ``prd/<id>-<slug>``. Surfaced as a helper so callers can compute\n100:    it before creating the ExecutionContext.\n101:    \"\"\"\n102:    return f\"prd/{prd.id}-{prd.slug}\"\n103:\n104:\n105:def _pick_model(task: AgentTask, prd: \"PRD\", override: str | None = None) -> str:\n106:    \"\"\"Resolve the model to use for an AgentTask invocation.\n107:\n108:    Priority: CLI override > task.model > capability-derived > sonnet.\n109:    \"\"\"\n110:    if override:\n111:        return override\n112:    if task.model:\n113:        return task.model\n114:    if task.model_from_capability:\n115:        return capability_to_model(prd.capability)\n116:    return \"sonnet\"\n117:\n118:\n119:def run_workflow(\n120:    prd: \"PRD\",\n121:    workflow: Workflow,\n122:    repo_root: Path,\n123:    base_ref: str,\n124:    *,\n125:    dry_run: bool = True,\n126:    model_override: str | None = None,\n127:    cli_timeout_minutes: int | None = None,\n128:    config_timeouts: dict | None = None,\n129:    styler: \"Styler | None\" = None,\n130:) -> RunResult:\n131:    \"\"\"Execute a workflow against a single PRD and return the result.\n132:\n133:    Builds an :class:`ExecutionContext` and dispatches each task in\n134:    ``workflow.tasks`` in order. Tasks mutate the context as they run\n135:    (set worktree path, store agent output, capture PR URL). On any\n136:    uncaught exception, returns a failure result with the partial\n137:    ``steps`` list so the caller can see what completed.\n138:\n139:    ``dry_run=True`` (default) makes every task log instead of\n140:    executing — safe to call on arbitrary PRDs.\n141:    \"\"\"\n142:    branch_name = _compute_branch_name(prd)\n143:    ctx = ExecutionContext(\n144:        prd=prd,\n145:        repo_root=repo_root,\n146:        workflow=workflow,\n147:        base_ref=base_ref,\n148:        branch_name=branch_name,\n149:        cwd=repo_root,\n150:        dry_run=dry_run,\n151:        logger=logger,\n152:    )\n153:\n154:    result = RunResult(success=True)\n155:    # Track the last AgentTask so a later ShellTask with\n156:    # on_failure=retry_agent can re-invoke it.\n157:    last_agent_task: AgentTask | None = None\n158:    last_agent_result: InvokeResult | None = None\n159:\n160:    try:\n161:        for task in workflow.tasks:\n162:            try:\n163:                step = _dispatch(\n164:                    task,\n165:                    ctx,\n166:                    model_override,\n167:                    last_agent_task,\n168:                    last_agent_result,\n169:                    cli_timeout_minutes=cli_timeout_minutes,\n170:                    config_timeouts=config_timeouts,\n171:                    styler=styler,\n172:                )\n173:                result.steps.append(step)\n174:\n175:                if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n176:                    last_agent_task = task\n177:                    # We can't easily reach the InvokeResult from _dispatch without\n178:                    # restructuring, so we re-record it here via a side channel:\n179:                    # _dispatch stores the agent result on the context.\n180:                    last_agent_result = getattr(ctx, \"_last_agent_result\", None)\n181:\n182:                if not step.success:\n183:                    result.success = False\n184:                    result.failure_reason = step.detail or f\"task {step.name!r} failed\"\n185:                    break\n186:            except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001 — we want to log any failure\n187:                result.success = False\n188:                result.failure_reason = f\"task {_task_name(task)!r} raised: {exc}\"\n189:                result.steps.append(\n190:                    TaskStep(\n191:                        name=_task_name(task),\n192:                        kind=_task_kind(task),\n193:                        success=False,\n194:                        detail=str(exc),\n195:                    )\n196:                )\n197:                break\n198:    finally:\n199:        _release_worktree_lock(ctx)\n200:\n201:    result.pr_url = ctx.pr_url\n202:    return result\n203:\n204:\n205:def _release_worktree_lock(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> None:\n206:    \"\"\"Release the advisory lock acquired by ensure_worktree, if any.\n207:\n208:    Safe to call multiple times and on contexts that never acquired a\n209:    lock (e.g. dry-run paths).\n210:    \"\"\"\n211:    lock = ctx._worktree_lock\n212:    if lock is None:\n213:        return\n214:    try:\n215:        lock.release()\n216:    except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n217:        ctx.logger.warning(\"failed to release worktree lock: %s\", exc)\n218:    finally:\n219:        ctx._worktree_lock = None\n220:\n221:\n222:def _task_name(task: Task) -> str:\n223:    if isinstance(task, BuiltIn):\n224:        return task.name\n225:    if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n226:        return task.name\n227:    if isinstance(task, ShellTask):\n228:        return task.name\n229:    return type(task).__name__\n230:\n231:\n232:def _task_kind(task: Task) -> str:\n233:    if isinstance(task, BuiltIn):\n234:        return \"builtin\"\n235:    if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n236:        return \"agent\"\n237:    if isinstance(task, ShellTask):\n238:        return \"shell\"\n239:    return \"unknown\"\n240:\n241:\n242:def _dispatch(\n243:    task: Task,\n244:    ctx: ExecutionContext,\n245:    model_override: str | None,\n246:    last_agent_task: AgentTask | None,\n247:    last_agent_result: InvokeResult | None,\n248:    *,\n249:    cli_timeout_minutes: int | None = None,\n250:    config_timeouts: dict | None = None,\n\n[Showing results with pagination = limit: 250]"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"085d0cd6-f2e2-4251-a646-1672302e8715","uuid":"4b996046-f0f7-40fb-8483-46ac45de0d3a","timestamp":"2026-04-09T03:47:49.256Z","tool_use_result":{"mode":"content","numFiles":0,"filenames":[],"content":"1:\"\"\"Workflow execution engine — walks a workflow's tasks against a context.\n2:\n3:The runner is the glue between every other module in the harness:\n4:\n5:- It holds an :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.ExecutionContext` and\n6:  threads it through the task list.\n7:- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.BuiltIn`, it looks up the\n8:  named function in :data:`~darkfactory.builtins.BUILTINS` and calls\n9:  it with the context + formatted kwargs.\n10:- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.AgentTask`, it composes the\n11:  prompt via :func:`~darkfactory.templates.compose_prompt`, picks the\n12:  model (explicit override > capability mapping > sonnet fallback),\n13:  invokes Claude Code via :func:`~darkfactory.invoke.invoke_claude`,\n14:  and stores the output on the context.\n15:- For each :class:`~darkfactory.workflow.ShellTask`, it runs the\n16:  formatted command and handles the configured ``on_failure`` policy.\n17:\n18:The runner does **not** know how to create branches, manage\n19:worktrees, or open PRs — those are built-in tasks. Its only job is\n20:the dispatch loop and the retry-on-failure bookkeeping.\n21:\n22:Retry semantics: when a ShellTask fails with\n23:``on_failure=\"retry_agent\"``, the runner looks backward in the task\n24:list for the most recent AgentTask, re-invokes it with the failed\n25:output bound to ``{{CHECK_OUTPUT}}``, and re-runs the failed shell\n26:task once. If it still fails, the runner gives up and marks the\n27:PRD blocked (via a separate ``set_status`` built-in call).\n28:\n29:Dry-run mode: when ``ctx.dry_run=True``, every built-in and shell\n30:task logs what it would do without executing. Agent tasks return a\n31:synthetic success result via :func:`~darkfactory.invoke.invoke_claude`'s\n32:``dry_run=True`` path. This is what ``prd plan`` uses.\n33:\"\"\"\n34:\n35:from __future__ import annotations\n36:\n37:import logging\n38:import subprocess\n39:from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n40:from pathlib import Path\n41:from typing import TYPE_CHECKING\n42:\n43:from .builtins import BUILTINS\n44:from .invoke import InvokeResult, capability_to_model, invoke_claude\n45:from .templates import compose_prompt\n46:from .timeouts import resolve_timeout\n47:from .workflow import (\n48:    AgentTask,\n49:    BuiltIn,\n50:    ExecutionContext,\n51:    ShellTask,\n52:    Task,\n53:    Workflow,\n54:)\n55:\n56:if TYPE_CHECKING:\n57:    from .prd import PRD\n58:    from .style import Styler\n59:\n60:\n61:logger = logging.getLogger(\"darkfactory.runner\")\n62:\n63:\n64:@dataclass\n65:class TaskStep:\n66:    \"\"\"A single executed task step and its outcome.\n67:\n68:    Used by :class:`RunResult` to record what actually happened during\n69:    a workflow run, for both success reporting and debugging failures.\n70:    \"\"\"\n71:\n72:    name: str\n73:    kind: str  # \"builtin\" | \"agent\" | \"shell\"\n74:    success: bool\n75:    detail: str = \"\"\n76:\n77:\n78:@dataclass\n79:class RunResult:\n80:    \"\"\"Structured outcome of a workflow run.\n81:\n82:    The runner populates this as it walks the task list. On success,\n83:    ``success=True`` and ``pr_url`` is set (assuming the workflow\n84:    includes a ``create_pr`` built-in). On failure, ``success=False``\n85:    and ``failure_reason`` describes what went wrong; ``steps`` is\n86:    still populated with every step that completed before the failure.\n87:    \"\"\"\n88:\n89:    success: bool\n90:    pr_url: str | None = None\n91:    steps: list[TaskStep] = field(default_factory=list)\n92:    failure_reason: str | None = None\n93:\n94:\n95:def _compute_branch_name(prd: \"PRD\") -> str:\n96:    \"\"\"Derive the branch name a workflow should use for this PRD.\n97:\n98:    Matches the convention in ``ensure_worktree``:\n99:    ``prd/<id>-<slug>``. Surfaced as a helper so callers can compute\n100:    it before creating the ExecutionContext.\n101:    \"\"\"\n102:    return f\"prd/{prd.id}-{prd.slug}\"\n103:\n104:\n105:def _pick_model(task: AgentTask, prd: \"PRD\", override: str | None = None) -> str:\n106:    \"\"\"Resolve the model to use for an AgentTask invocation.\n107:\n108:    Priority: CLI override > task.model > capability-derived > sonnet.\n109:    \"\"\"\n110:    if override:\n111:        return override\n112:    if task.model:\n113:        return task.model\n114:    if task.model_from_capability:\n115:        return capability_to_model(prd.capability)\n116:    return \"sonnet\"\n117:\n118:\n119:def run_workflow(\n120:    prd: \"PRD\",\n121:    workflow: Workflow,\n122:    repo_root: Path,\n123:    base_ref: str,\n124:    *,\n125:    dry_run: bool = True,\n126:    model_override: str | None = None,\n127:    cli_timeout_minutes: int | None = None,\n128:    config_timeouts: dict | None = None,\n129:    styler: \"Styler | None\" = None,\n130:) -> RunResult:\n131:    \"\"\"Execute a workflow against a single PRD and return the result.\n132:\n133:    Builds an :class:`ExecutionContext` and dispatches each task in\n134:    ``workflow.tasks`` in order. Tasks mutate the context as they run\n135:    (set worktree path, store agent output, capture PR URL). On any\n136:    uncaught exception, returns a failure result with the partial\n137:    ``steps`` list so the caller can see what completed.\n138:\n139:    ``dry_run=True`` (default) makes every task log instead of\n140:    executing — safe to call on arbitrary PRDs.\n141:    \"\"\"\n142:    branch_name = _compute_branch_name(prd)\n143:    ctx = ExecutionContext(\n144:        prd=prd,\n145:        repo_root=repo_root,\n146:        workflow=workflow,\n147:        base_ref=base_ref,\n148:        branch_name=branch_name,\n149:        cwd=repo_root,\n150:        dry_run=dry_run,\n151:        logger=logger,\n152:    )\n153:\n154:    result = RunResult(success=True)\n155:    # Track the last AgentTask so a later ShellTask with\n156:    # on_failure=retry_agent can re-invoke it.\n157:    last_agent_task: AgentTask | None = None\n158:    last_agent_result: InvokeResult | None = None\n159:\n160:    try:\n161:        for task in workflow.tasks:\n162:            try:\n163:                step = _dispatch(\n164:                    task,\n165:                    ctx,\n166:                    model_override,\n167:                    last_agent_task,\n168:                    last_agent_result,\n169:                    cli_timeout_minutes=cli_timeout_minutes,\n170:                    config_timeouts=config_timeouts,\n171:                    styler=styler,\n172:                )\n173:                result.steps.append(step)\n174:\n175:                if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n176:                    last_agent_task = task\n177:                    # We can't easily reach the InvokeResult from _dispatch without\n178:                    # restructuring, so we re-record it here via a side channel:\n179:                    # _dispatch stores the agent result on the context.\n180:                    last_agent_result = getattr(ctx, \"_last_agent_result\", None)\n181:\n182:                if not step.success:\n183:                    result.success = False\n184:                    result.failure_reason = step.detail or f\"task {step.name!r} failed\"\n185:                    break\n186:            except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001 — we want to log any failure\n187:                result.success = False\n188:                result.failure_reason = f\"task {_task_name(task)!r} raised: {exc}\"\n189:                result.steps.append(\n190:                    TaskStep(\n191:                        name=_task_name(task),\n192:                        kind=_task_kind(task),\n193:                        success=False,\n194:                        detail=str(exc),\n195:                    )\n196:                )\n197:                break\n198:    finally:\n199:        _release_worktree_lock(ctx)\n200:\n201:    result.pr_url = ctx.pr_url\n202:    return result\n203:\n204:\n205:def _release_worktree_lock(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> None:\n206:    \"\"\"Release the advisory lock acquired by ensure_worktree, if any.\n207:\n208:    Safe to call multiple times and on contexts that never acquired a\n209:    lock (e.g. dry-run paths).\n210:    \"\"\"\n211:    lock = ctx._worktree_lock\n212:    if lock is None:\n213:        return\n214:    try:\n215:        lock.release()\n216:    except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n217:        ctx.logger.warning(\"failed to release worktree lock: %s\", exc)\n218:    finally:\n219:        ctx._worktree_lock = None\n220:\n221:\n222:def _task_name(task: Task) -> str:\n223:    if isinstance(task, BuiltIn):\n224:        return task.name\n225:    if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n226:        return task.name\n227:    if isinstance(task, ShellTask):\n228:        return task.name\n229:    return type(task).__name__\n230:\n231:\n232:def _task_kind(task: Task) -> str:\n233:    if isinstance(task, BuiltIn):\n234:        return \"builtin\"\n235:    if isinstance(task, AgentTask):\n236:        return \"agent\"\n237:    if isinstance(task, ShellTask):\n238:        return \"shell\"\n239:    return \"unknown\"\n240:\n241:\n242:def _dispatch(\n243:    task: Task,\n244:    ctx: ExecutionContext,\n245:    model_override: str | None,\n246:    last_agent_task: AgentTask | None,\n247:    last_agent_result: InvokeResult | None,\n248:    *,\n249:    cli_timeout_minutes: int | None = None,\n250:    config_timeouts: dict | None = None,","numLines":250,"appliedLimit":250}}
